    <!-- google_ad_section_start --><p>So <a href="https://drupal.org/project/kalatheme" target="_blank">Kalatheme</a> "ships with many responsive layouts, templates and tools right out of the box" and is built right on top of <a href="https://drupal.org/project/panopoly" target="_blank">Panopoly</a> (think responsive panels, panelizer...). But I used the built in Media capabilities to stick a video field into a news article application, and it was stuck in big. So I got a quick fix from <a href="http://avexdesigns.com/responsive-youtube-embed/" target="_blank">this article</a> by&nbsp;John Surdakowski, and applied it in just a few lines of CSS in my Kalatheme based sub-theme's css/main.css file:</p>
<pre>/* Responsive you-tube video */
.media-youtube-video {
	position:relative;
	padding-bottom:56.25%;
	padding-top:30px;
	height:0;
	overflow:hidden;
}
.media-youtube-video iframe {
  position:absolute;
  top:0;
  left:0;
  width:100%;
  height:100%;
}</pre><p>This is a bare-bones approach, but works splendidly in Kalatheme, and should work with other module sets and themes also, after having identified the iframe container div classes, and the appropriate iframe classes.</p>
